Here’s a **minimal print‑optimized CSS extension** you can layer on top of the regular stylesheet.  
It ensures clean margins, legible text size, and hides interactive disclosure icons when exporting LMS pages to PDF or physical printouts.

```css
/* supportive-conversation-print.css
   Optional print optimization for the Supportive‑Conversation Trainer’s Sheet
   Keeps structure readable and removes symbols that don't translate to paper.
*/

@media print {
  /* Page margins and font adjustments */
  body {
    margin: 1in;
    font-size: 11pt;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: #000;
  }

  /* Remove disclosure triangles and simplify summaries */
  details[open] summary::before,
  details summary::before {
    content: "";
  }

  /* Prevent collapsed text from being hidden in printed version */
  details summary + * {
    display: block !important;
  }

  /* Table borders slightly thicker for clarity */
  table, th, td {
    border: 1.5px solid #000;
  }

  /* Footer styling for print */
  footer {
    font-size: 9pt;
    color: #000;
    border-top: 1px solid #000;
    margin-top: 1em;
    padding-top: 0.5em;
  }
}
```

**Usage:**  
Add this second link in your HTML header after the main stylesheet:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="supportive-conversation.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="supportive-conversation-print.css" media="print">
```

This keeps on‑screen interactivity intact while ensuring clear, formal print exports with all sections expanded.

